---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = "The Studio — Aenea | Boutique Branding & UX/UI Design Studio, Norway";
const description = "Aenea is a boutique branding and UX/UI studio in Norway — founded on restraint, strategy, and detail. Working with architecture studios, hotels, and design-led brands on brand identities and websites built to last.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Navbar current="studio" />

  <main>
    <section class="studio-hero wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Studio</span>
      <h1 class="studio-title">The studio behind the work.</h1>
      <p class="studio-lead">Aenea is a boutique branding and UX/UI studio in Norway — built on the belief that great design is never just visual. It&rsquo;s structural, it&rsquo;s strategic, and it&rsquo;s the result of paying attention to what most people overlook.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="statement wrap">
      <p class="statement-lead">I started this studio to work differently — closely, carefully, and only on projects I could fully commit to. Not a production line. A practice.</p>
      <p class="statement-body">The name Aenea carries a sense of purpose and permanence. That&rsquo;s intentional: everything I design is built to hold — across time, across touchpoints, across contexts.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="case wrap">
      <div class="case-label"><span class="idx">01</span><span class="eyebrow">How I Work</span></div>
      <div class="case-body">
        <p>Design, for me, begins long before anything is placed on a canvas. It begins with understanding — the brand, the audience, and the gap between where a business is and where it wants to be. From there, every decision has a reason: every typeface, every margin, every colour choice in service of something larger than aesthetics.</p>
        <p>I studied design formally and have spent years refining what that education gave me — learning to trust restraint, to value atmosphere, and to understand that the details clients rarely notice are often the ones that make everything feel right.</p>
        <p>Precision matters. Process matters. And so does the relationship — because the best work always comes from genuine collaboration, not just a brief and a deadline.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case wrap">
      <div class="case-label"><span class="idx">02</span><span class="eyebrow">Who I Work With</span></div>
      <div class="case-body">
        <p>I work with architecture studios, hotels, restaurants, jewellery brands, and beauty spaces — businesses where design is already part of the offer, not an afterthought.</p>
        <p>These are clients who understand that visual identity shapes perception before a single conversation takes place. That a website earns trust or loses it in seconds. That consistency isn&rsquo;t rigidity — it&rsquo;s confidence.</p>
        <p>I take on a small number of clients at a time. A deliberate choice: it means every project gets full attention, honest thinking, and work I&rsquo;d put my name on — because I do.</p>
        <ul class="sectors">
          <li><span class="s-idx">01</span> Architecture studios</li>
          <li><span class="s-idx">02</span> Hotels &amp; hospitality</li>
          <li><span class="s-idx">03</span> Restaurants</li>
          <li><span class="s-idx">04</span> Jewellery brands</li>
          <li><span class="s-idx">05</span> Beauty spaces</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="quote-band">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="quote">I&rsquo;m not interested in design that simply looks good. I&rsquo;m interested in design that works — and still looks good five years from now.</p>
        <span class="quote-by">Aenea</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="studio-cta wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Get in touch</span>
      <h2>Let&rsquo;s build something worth keeping.</h2>
      <p>If you&rsquo;re working on a brand, a website, or a visual system that deserves real attention, I&rsquo;d like to hear about it.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="/#contact">Start a conversation <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>